- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses regularization of Laplacian matrices, which is a fundamental concept in linear algebra and graph theory.
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the term "spectral" can also refer to the analysis of sound signals.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves numerical optimization to determine the optimal regularization.
